es have been deeply consequential, and Mueggler traces the transformations they have wrought and their lasting effects.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aDeathzChina, Southwest. 0aDeath-China, Southwest. 0aFuneral rites and ceremonieszChina, Southwest. 0aFuneral rites and ceremonies-China, Southwest. 0aMourning customszChina, Southwest. 0aMourning customs-China, Southwest. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aChina.  aDeath.  aYi.  aYunnan.  aembodiment.  aghosts.  amaterialization.  aritual.  asocialism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226483412423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226483412/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles